  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "note_30",
      "text": "Fits a cosine model to a rhythmic series by least squares, returning MESOR (rhythm-adjusted mean), amplitude, acrophase and period, with an F-test / R² and optional permutation p-value. Use it for approximately sinusoidal rhythms when you want interpretable rhythm parameters and a significance test; a fixed period (e.g. 24 h) turns it into linear single/multi-harmonic cosinor, while leaving the period free fits it. In the demo, read the fitted smooth cosine overlaid on the raw points: peak height is the amplitude, the peak's time-of-day is the acrophase, and the horizontal midline is the MESOR. Method: cosinor rhythmometry (Cornélissen 2014).",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 24,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 190
    }
  ],
